@@TJvSerialDlg
<TITLEIMG TJvSerialDlg>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.Dialogs.Custom
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  Displays a dialog for entering a name and serial key.
Description
  The TJvSerialDlg component displays a modal dialog box that prompts the user for a name and 
  serial key \string. The dialog does not appear at runtime until it is activated by a call to the 
  Execute method.
  
  The purpose of this dialog box is to let a user specify a name and serial key. You use the Execute
  method to display the dialog box.
  When the user chooses OK in the dialog box, the entered name and serial key are stored in the 
  NameValue and SerialValue properties, resp., which you can then process as you want.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvSerialDlg.Execute
Summary
  Displays the dialog box for entering a name and serial key.
Description
  Execute opens the dialog for entering a name and serial key.
Returns
  Returns True when the user clicks the "OK" button and False when the user clicks Cancel.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvSerialDlg.FirstLabel
Summary
  Specifies the text in the dialog's name label.
Description
  Use SecondLabel to specify the text that appears in the label above the edit box where the user can
  enter a name. If no value is assigned to SecondLabel, the label has the caption "<U>N</U>ame:".
See Also
  SecondLabel, Title
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvSerialDlg.NameValue
Summary
  Returns the entered name.
Description
  When the user enters a name in the dialog box and clicks OK, the entered name becomes the value
  of the NameValue property. To make a default name of choice appear in the dialog when it opens, assign
  a value to NameValue in the Object Inspector or in program code, otherwise the default is "".
See Also
  SerialValue
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvSerialDlg.SecondLabel
Summary
  Specifies the text in the dialog's serial label.
Description
  Use SecondLabel to specify the text that appears in the label above the edit box where the user can
  enter a serial key. If no value is assigned to SecondLabel, the label has the caption "<U>S</U>erial:".
See Also
  FirstLabel, Title
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvSerialDlg.SerialValue
Summary
  Returns the entered serial key.
Description
  When the user enters a serial key in the dialog box and clicks OK, the entered value becomes the value
  of the SerialValue property. To make a default serial key of choice appear in the dialog when it opens, assign
  a value to SerialValue in the Object Inspector or in program code, otherwise the default is "".
See Also
  NameValue
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvSerialDlg.Title
Summary
  Specifies the text in the dialog’s title bar.
Description
  Use Title to specify the text that appears in the dialog’s title bar. If no value 
  is assigned to Title, the dialog has the title "Enter Serial".
See Also
  FirstLabel, SecondLabel
